oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: German bank note, 50,000 RM
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Fifty-thousand-mark Reichsbank note is printed in green and brown, and on the front is an engraving of von Brauweiler. Below that is serial number C-04309463. Backside printed with the note's denomination. Von Brauweiler was elected mayor of Cologne in 1516, and he adamantly opposed the Reformation. The note came home with U.S. Capt, William L. Thomas, HQ Bttry., 879th FA BN., 69th Inf. Div., after World War II.
